15
00:01:31,530 --> 00:01:35,320
What will you do now? Huh?

16
00:01:36,770 --> 00:01:38,560
What will you do now?

17
00:01:38,560 --> 00:01:40,370
- Mom... 
 - What will you do now?

18
00:01:40,370 --> 00:01:42,740
What are you doing, Mom?

19
00:01:42,740 --> 00:01:46,820
Pil Sung, that bitch abandoned you in front of our house!

20
00:01:46,820 --> 00:01:53,170
When you were less than a week old, that bitch abandoned you in front of our house!

21
00:01:58,420 --> 00:02:00,330
No way.

22
00:02:02,320 --> 00:02:05,890
This bitch abandoned a baby?

23
00:02:05,890 --> 00:02:09,780
And he was even less than a week old?

24
00:02:09,780 --> 00:02:13,370
Aigoo, what a horrible bitch!

25
00:02:13,370 --> 00:02:18,760
You bitch! How did you abandon your baby?

26
00:02:19,950 --> 00:02:26,410
♪  Until the East Sea's waves are dry, Mt. Baekdu worn away  ♪  

27
00:02:26,410 --> 00:02:30,480
How dare you! How dare you do that...

28
00:02:37,930 --> 00:02:41,870
Director, where's my Ji Yeong?

29
00:02:41,870 --> 00:02:44,210
Director.

30
00:02:45,260 --> 00:02:47,980
Just one moment, Grandma. I'll take you to Ji Yeong.

31
00:02:47,980 --> 00:02:50,930
- Please wait just a moment. 
 - Okay.

32
00:03:12,100 --> 00:03:14,800
Yes, Director.

33
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:16,720
Ji Yeong, where are you right now?

34
00:03:16,720 --> 00:03:18,680
I'm at home.

35
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:20,810
What's this about?

36
00:03:20,810 --> 00:03:23,020
Your grandmother came here.

37
00:03:23,020 --> 00:03:25,270
W-What did you say?

38
00:03:25,270 --> 00:03:27,660
My grandma went to your house?

39
00:03:27,660 --> 00:03:32,170
Yes, but I think her dementia is kicking in.

40
00:03:32,170 --> 00:03:34,700
She's singing, looking for you right now.

41
00:03:34,700 --> 00:03:38,230
Oh, my gosh. I'm so sorry, but...

42
00:03:38,230 --> 00:03:40,830
please make sure she doesn't go anywhere.

43
00:03:40,830 --> 00:03:42,280
I'll be there right now.

44
00:03:42,280 --> 00:03:44,750
No, I think it'd be faster if I went.

45
00:03:44,750 --> 00:03:46,640
She's looking for you so desperately.

46
00:03:46,640 --> 00:03:48,990
I'll get going right now.

47
00:03:48,990 --> 00:03:51,030
Okay. Gosh...

48
00:03:51,030 --> 00:03:54,210
Gosh! What do I do with her?

49
00:04:07,780 --> 00:04:09,480
Ji Yeong!

50
00:04:09,480 --> 00:04:11,460
Grandma!

51
00:04:11,460 --> 00:04:13,200
- Ji Yeong! 
 - Yes.

52
00:04:14,170 --> 00:04:15,550
Let me see.

53
00:04:15,550 --> 00:04:17,260
Are you back to your senses?

54
00:04:17,260 --> 00:04:18,580
Yes.

55
00:04:18,580 --> 00:04:22,350
I heard you sang the national anthem at the Director's house.

56
00:04:22,350 --> 00:04:26,810
Yes, I think I lost my mind again.

57
00:04:26,810 --> 00:04:29,100
Why did you come alone without telling me?

58
00:04:29,100 --> 00:04:31,260
What if you got lost?

59
00:04:31,260 --> 00:04:34,230
What if you lost your mind in someone else's house?

60
00:04:34,230 --> 00:04:37,860
Hey, I don't just do that in any situation.

61
00:04:37,860 --> 00:04:40,660
I don't do that at a random place.

62
00:04:40,660 --> 00:04:42,730
Are you joking right now?

63
00:04:42,730 --> 00:04:45,180
This could've been really bad!

64
00:04:45,180 --> 00:04:48,210
Anyway, when did you move?

65
00:04:48,210 --> 00:04:51,510
How come you didn't tell me?

66
00:04:55,360 --> 00:04:58,990
Well, the thing is...

67
00:05:00,140 --> 00:05:04,870
Grandma, I'll explain that to you after we go inside.

68
00:05:04,870 --> 00:05:07,280
- Let's go inside. 
 - Okay, okay.

69
00:05:07,280 --> 00:05:12,430
Director, I'm so sorry about today.

70
00:05:12,430 --> 00:05:15,600
- Thank you. 
 - Don't mention it.

71
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:18,160
Oh, just one second.

72
00:05:21,460 --> 00:05:24,750
What's with you?

73
00:05:24,750 --> 00:05:26,910
Seriously.

74
00:05:28,150 --> 00:05:32,270
- Take these... 
 - Ji Yeong, she brought these with her.

75
00:05:32,270 --> 00:05:34,350
I'll get going now.

76
00:05:34,350 --> 00:05:37,070
Thank you, Director.

77
00:05:37,070 --> 00:05:41,100
Thank you so much for driving her here.

78
00:05:44,110 --> 00:05:46,150
I'll get going, Ma'am.

79
00:05:46,150 --> 00:05:49,700
Okay. See you next time, then.

80
00:05:49,700 --> 00:05:51,170
Yes.

81
00:05:53,690 --> 00:05:55,140
Go inside.

82
00:06:08,310 --> 00:06:11,960
What? Grandma? The grandma from the countryside?

83
00:06:11,960 --> 00:06:15,390
Yes, she came because she missed me.

84
00:06:15,390 --> 00:06:20,930
Yes, I kept seeing her in my dreams.

85
00:06:20,930 --> 00:06:25,310
I missed her and was curious about her. So I came.

86
00:06:25,310 --> 00:06:31,800
 Gosh, is she the old lady who rescued Do Ra and got her treated? 

87
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:34,500
- Have a seat, Grandma. 
 - Okay, okay.

88
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:36,820
I'll get you something to drink.

89
00:06:36,820 --> 00:06:38,500
Okay.

90
00:06:42,110 --> 00:06:47,820
By the way, are you really Ji Yeong's boss?

91
00:06:47,820 --> 00:06:51,520
Yes, I am Ji Yeong's boss.

92
00:06:51,520 --> 00:06:56,810
I've been training her while living with her here.

93
00:06:56,810 --> 00:07:00,480
I see. Train... or whatever.

94
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:05,180
By the way, on TV...

95
00:07:05,180 --> 00:07:11,000
CEO's houses are huge and flashy.

96
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:15,690
Yes, I used to be successful once, too.

97
00:07:16,340 --> 00:07:18,440
Grandma, drink this.

98
00:07:18,440 --> 00:07:20,570
Okay, okay, okay.

99
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:24,720
By the way, Ji Yeong,

100
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:28,300
can't you just live at the Director's house?

101
00:07:28,300 --> 00:07:31,510
It's a nice and spacious place.

102
00:07:31,510 --> 00:07:37,220
Do you really have to live here with her?

103
00:07:37,220 --> 00:07:41,100
She'd find it uncomfortable, too.

104
00:07:41,100 --> 00:07:44,220
I don't think this is right.

105
00:07:44,220 --> 00:07:47,000
That's not true, Grandma.

106
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:51,070
She's a good acting coach, too.

107
00:07:51,070 --> 00:07:53,250
So I need to live here.

108
00:07:53,250 --> 00:07:58,630
♫  Until the East Sea's waves are dry, Mt. Baekdu worn away  ♫

109
00:07:58,630 --> 00:08:00,600
What's wrong with her?

110
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:04,540
♫  - God watches over our land forever  ♫ 
 - She does this...

111
00:08:04,540 --> 00:08:07,890
♫  - Bless Korea  ♫ 
 - whenever she has dementia episodes.

112
00:08:07,890 --> 00:08:09,840
- I'm home. 
 - Huh?

113
00:08:09,840 --> 00:08:11,590
Do Sik.

114
00:08:11,590 --> 00:08:13,730
My gosh, Geum Dong!

115
00:08:13,730 --> 00:08:15,650
Gosh, my Geum Dong's here.

116
00:08:15,650 --> 00:08:18,140
Gosh, Geum Dong!

117
00:08:18,910 --> 00:08:24,340
Geum Dong, you must be tired from working all day.

118
00:08:25,270 --> 00:08:28,000
Hey! What are you doing?

119
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:31,850
Your husband is here. Won't you prepare a meal?

120
00:08:31,850 --> 00:08:33,940
Geum Dong, wait just a moment.

121
00:08:33,940 --> 00:08:37,210
I'll get you some cold water.

122
00:08:42,530 --> 00:08:46,090
So, are you saying she has dementia?

123
00:08:46,090 --> 00:08:51,200
Yes, she was improving for a while, but I think she got worse.

124
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:53,390
What do we do with her?

125
00:08:53,390 --> 00:08:55,740
Who's Geum Dong, then?

126
00:08:55,740 --> 00:08:58,300
My dad. My dad, who passed away.

127
00:08:58,300 --> 00:09:00,800
She thinks I'm her son right now, then?

128
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:02,440
Yes, I think so.

129
00:09:02,440 --> 00:09:05,810
I think she thinks Ahjumma is my mom.

130
00:09:05,810 --> 00:09:07,580
Stepmom.

131
00:09:08,300 --> 00:09:11,280
This isn't good. We should send her to a nursing home.

132
00:09:11,280 --> 00:09:14,510
You can't handle something like that at home.

133
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:20,050
No! How could I send her to a nursing home?

134
00:09:20,050 --> 00:09:23,490
She's the reason I'm alive now.

135
00:09:23,490 --> 00:09:27,980
What do we do, then? We need to shoot the show and live together.

136
00:09:27,980 --> 00:09:32,680
I'll find an apartment and live with her, then.

137
00:09:32,680 --> 00:09:34,640
You can't do that!

138
00:09:35,530 --> 00:09:38,720
We finally found each other. How can we live separately?

139
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:41,550
And you're my daughter. We need to live together.

140
00:09:41,550 --> 00:09:43,940
Yes, Do Ra. I mean, Ji Yeong.

141
00:09:43,940 --> 00:09:45,470
Why should we be separated again?

142
00:09:45,470 --> 00:09:47,410
That makes no sense.

143
00:09:48,430 --> 00:09:50,080
- Mom. 
 - Yes?

144
00:09:50,080 --> 00:09:53,820
We should just all live here together with her.

145
00:09:54,720 --> 00:09:58,840
- What? 
 - She saved Ji Yeong. We owe her.

146
00:09:58,840 --> 00:10:01,680
We'd be returning the favor that way.

147
00:10:01,680 --> 00:10:04,510
- Gosh, seriously... 
 - Quit complaining.

148
00:10:04,510 --> 00:10:06,490
This is my apartment.

149
00:10:09,390 --> 00:10:11,020
That's true.

150
00:10:12,620 --> 00:10:16,070
 Pil Sung, that bitch abandoned you in front of our house! 

151
00:10:16,070 --> 00:10:22,390
 When you were less than a week old, that bitch abandoned you in front of our house! 

152
00:11:03,390 --> 00:11:05,820
I can't take it anymore.

153
00:11:05,820 --> 00:11:08,900
It's true you did the wrong thing, but still.

154
00:11:08,900 --> 00:11:14,250
I can't let them do this to you anymore.

155
00:11:14,250 --> 00:11:17,320
I'm really okay, Ma Ri.

156
00:11:18,580 --> 00:11:20,730
But...

157
00:11:20,730 --> 00:11:23,440
But Pil Sung found out.

158
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:25,530
Pil Sung did.

159
00:11:26,350 --> 00:11:28,700
What do we do now?

160
00:11:28,700 --> 00:11:31,400
- What am I supposed to do? 
 - What?

161
00:11:32,130 --> 00:11:36,720
O-Oppa found out?

162
00:11:48,640 --> 00:11:50,190
   

163
00:11:56,360 --> 00:12:00,610
Yes, Pil Sung. I-It's me.

164
00:12:18,680 --> 00:12:20,500
You came.

165
00:12:27,670 --> 00:12:29,940
What I heard earlier...

166
00:12:30,740 --> 00:12:32,590
Is it all true?

167
00:12:33,370 --> 00:12:35,910
I came to confirm it myself.

168
00:12:36,490 --> 00:12:39,550
Are you my biological mother...

169
00:12:42,020 --> 00:12:43,690
