I'm so happy to see you right now.

532
00:39:03,916 --> 00:39:05,646
Ma Ri,

533
00:39:06,646 --> 00:39:10,286
thank you so much for understanding.

534
00:39:10,286 --> 00:39:15,936
But hearing that you're sick and you can't eat anything

535
00:39:15,936 --> 00:39:19,396
upsets me so much.

536
00:39:19,396 --> 00:39:23,710
You need to eat well and be healthy at times like this.

537
00:39:24,386 --> 00:39:26,176
I'm sorry.

538
00:39:26,176 --> 00:39:30,106
But I can't eat anything right now.

539
00:39:30,106 --> 00:39:32,676
I can't bring myself to swallow food.

540
00:39:35,136 --> 00:39:38,616
What do we do with poor Ma Ri?

541
00:39:40,236 --> 00:39:42,726
Gosh, Ma Ri.

542
00:39:46,566 --> 00:39:49,336
 The poor kid is suffering so much. 

543
00:39:52,856 --> 00:39:54,986
Mom, what are you talking about?

544
00:39:54,986 --> 00:39:57,036
You want us to forgive Ma Ri?

545
00:39:57,036 --> 00:39:59,876
I heard she can't even eat.

546
00:39:59,876 --> 00:40:03,116
So, I steamed a few cobs of corn for her.

547
00:40:03,116 --> 00:40:06,216
But she was so pitiful.

548
00:40:06,216 --> 00:40:09,796
I couldn't bear to look at her.

549
00:40:09,796 --> 00:40:15,436
She knows she can't see Oppa anymore and she knows she can't come to our house,

550
00:40:15,436 --> 00:40:18,156
but that makes her so sad.

551
00:40:18,156 --> 00:40:23,846
She was happy to have an older brother, but she was told she couldn't see him anymore.

552
00:40:23,846 --> 00:40:26,536
She said, "I have no hope to go on."

553
00:40:27,336 --> 00:40:30,676
She was crying a river saying that.

554
00:40:30,676 --> 00:40:35,556
I ended up crying with her, too, since I felt so bad.

555
00:40:35,556 --> 00:40:40,176
Gosh, seriously. Why would you pity her, anyway?

556
00:40:40,176 --> 00:40:47,030
The one who deserves the most pity is her,

557
00:40:53,276 --> 00:41:00,170
Seon Yeong,

558
00:41:00,170 --> 00:41:02,096
I hate her, too.

559
00:41:02,096 --> 00:41:04,586
She still gives me chills.

560
00:41:04,586 --> 00:41:06,666
But not Ma Ri.

561
00:41:06,666 --> 00:41:09,096
What did Ma Ri do, exactly?

562
00:41:09,096 --> 00:41:13,616
She likes Pil Sung because she feels connected to him.

563
00:41:13,616 --> 00:41:17,466
She says she just loves him so much.

564
00:41:18,266 --> 00:41:23,586
Separating siblings like that doesn't seem right to me.

565
00:41:24,526 --> 00:41:30,586
Seon Yeong, you might find this hurtful, but

566
00:41:30,586 --> 00:41:32,666
I'm planning to tell...

567
00:41:32,666 --> 00:41:35,756
Pil Sung that Ma Ri's very sick

568
00:41:35,756 --> 00:41:41,716
and he should be in touch with her from now on.

569
00:41:41,716 --> 00:41:43,986
Mother.

570
00:41:43,986 --> 00:41:49,966
For Pil Sung, Ma Ri is his only sibling in this entire world.

571
00:41:49,966 --> 00:41:56,106
But if you're unwilling to accept Ma Ri, how is that fair to Pil Sung?

572
00:41:58,716 --> 00:42:02,146
She's his only sibling in this world.

573
00:42:02,146 --> 00:42:04,436
And she's even sick right now.

574
00:42:04,436 --> 00:42:10,306
How hurt and tormented must he feel if he can't see her?

575
00:42:10,306 --> 00:42:11,986
Don't you think?

576
00:42:13,556 --> 00:42:20,406
Unni, I think we should forgive Ma Ri after hearing Mom.

577
00:42:20,406 --> 00:42:23,146
For Pil Sung's sake, too.

578
00:42:34,146 --> 00:42:37,576
Ma Ri's sick?

579
00:42:38,586 --> 00:42:40,916
Did you meet Ma Ri, Grandma?

580
00:42:40,916 --> 00:42:46,346
Yes, her mom came by and said she was extremely sick.

581
00:42:46,346 --> 00:42:51,026
She cried and begged us to forgive just Ma Ri.

582
00:42:51,926 --> 00:42:54,616
How could I not visit her?

583
00:42:55,166 --> 00:42:59,926
So, I went to see how she was doing.

584
00:43:00,626 --> 00:43:02,960
As her mom said, she can't eat anything.

585
00:43:02,960 --> 00:43:06,010
She's barely hanging in there.

586
00:43:07,386 --> 00:43:13,806
She was so happy to have an older brother, but she's sad because she can't see him anymore.

587
00:43:14,296 --> 00:43:16,896
She said she had no hope to go on.

588
00:43:18,476 --> 00:43:20,576
Did she...

589
00:43:20,576 --> 00:43:22,586
Did she say that?

590
00:43:32,450 --> 00:43:34,550
   

591
00:43:38,856 --> 00:43:40,516
Ma Ri!

592
00:43:42,716 --> 00:43:45,246
Ma Ri, are you okay?

593
00:43:45,246 --> 00:43:46,786
Yes.

594
00:43:49,436 --> 00:43:55,266
I'm sorry, Oppa. I'm sorry I was peeping at you.

595
00:43:55,716 --> 00:43:56,966
What?

596
00:43:56,966 --> 00:43:59,326
I'm sorry. I came because I missed you so much.

597
00:43:59,326 --> 00:44:01,516
I won't come back again.

598
00:44:02,196 --> 00:44:04,156
Ma Ri, hold on.

599
00:44:05,896 --> 00:44:08,006
Should we talk for a moment?

600
00:44:12,306 --> 00:44:16,046
Gong Ma Ri, I heard you were very sick.

601
00:44:16,046 --> 00:44:19,146
No. No, I wasn't.

602
00:44:22,756 --> 00:44:27,476
- Ma Ri. 
 - I will never visit you ever again.

603
00:44:27,476 --> 00:44:29,526
I promise.

604
00:44:31,606 --> 00:44:36,226
Ma Ri, I thought about you a lot, too.

605
00:44:38,546 --> 00:44:40,826
You thought about me?

606
00:44:42,166 --> 00:44:44,946
What do you mean?

607
00:44:45,666 --> 00:44:50,486
You felt familiar when I first saw you

608
00:44:50,486 --> 00:44:56,106
and even when you were chasing me, I felt like you were a cute younger sister.

609
00:44:56,106 --> 00:44:58,046
Really?

610
00:45:05,026 --> 00:45:08,596
I hate the fact that your mom is my biological mother,

611
00:45:10,126 --> 00:45:12,676
and I can't forgive her.

612
00:45:12,676 --> 00:45:14,746
You know why, right?

613
00:45:14,746 --> 00:45:19,296
Yes, I do. That makes sense completely.

614
00:45:19,296 --> 00:45:23,606
I still can't forgive her, either.

615
00:45:25,406 --> 00:45:27,936
But you're my younger sister.

616
00:45:30,106 --> 00:45:32,616
I'm happy that you're my sister.

617
00:45:34,116 --> 00:45:35,886
Really?

618
00:45:38,416 --> 00:45:40,956
So, I'd like to see you sometimes.

619
00:45:40,956 --> 00:45:42,996
Because you're my younger sister.

620
00:45:44,046 --> 00:45:45,986
What do you think?

621
00:45:45,986 --> 00:45:49,716
I'd love to. I'd really, really love to.

622
00:45:50,616 --> 00:45:53,296
Thank you, Oppa.

623
00:45:53,296 --> 00:45:56,976
Thank you. Thank you so much.

624
00:46:03,726 --> 00:46:06,196
W-What did you say?

625
00:46:06,196 --> 00:46:08,706
You'd keep in touch with Ma Ri?

626
00:46:08,706 --> 00:46:11,456
Pil Sung, how could you say that in front of Mom?

627
00:46:11,456 --> 00:46:13,276
Hold on.

628
00:46:13,276 --> 00:46:15,876
He's not done talking yet.

629
00:46:17,126 --> 00:46:19,546
Yes, go on, Pil Sung.

630
00:46:21,096 --> 00:46:24,390
I'm not willing to forgive President Jang, either.

631
00:46:24,976 --> 00:46:30,396
But the fact that Ma Ri is my sister is undeniable.

632
00:46:31,176 --> 00:46:34,926
She came by to peep at me earlier, too.

633
00:46:35,596 --> 00:46:39,136
I don't want to ignore her heartfelt feelings.

634
00:46:39,136 --> 00:46:45,226
Gosh, she was following you around, saying, "Oppa, Oppa."

635
00:46:45,226 --> 00:46:49,496
She visited you in that condition?

636
00:46:49,496 --> 00:46:55,536
Gosh, I feel so bad for Ma Ri. Seriously.

637
00:46:55,536 --> 00:47:00,246
Mom, be quiet at times like this. You're making it worse.

638
00:47:01,446 --> 00:47:04,576
Mom, Father,

639
00:47:04,576 --> 00:47:09,916
I'd like your permission to see Ma Ri.

640
00:47:09,916 --> 00:47:13,936
I don't want to see her secretly if you don't want me to.

641
00:47:17,496 --> 00:47:19,566
Yes.

642
00:47:19,566 --> 00:47:21,446
Go ahead.

643
00:47:22,486 --> 00:47:25,696
Honey, w-would you be okay?

644
00:47:28,266 --> 00:47:34,866
If I told Pil Sung to ignore his sister, Ma Ri,

645
00:47:34,866 --> 00:47:36,956
I'd be no different from Jang Soo Yeon.

646
00:47:36,956 --> 00:47:39,436
Ma Ri didn't do anything wrong.

647
00:47:42,166 --> 00:47:43,706
Mom.

648
00:47:46,076 --> 00:47:48,896
Do what you want to do, Pil Sung.

649
00:47:50,786 --> 00:47:52,586
Thank you.

650
00:48:03,386 --> 00:48:04,686
   

651
00:48:04,686 --> 00:48:06,126
Yes, I'm heading over, too.

652
00:48:06,126 --> 00:48:08,596
Yes, see you on set.

653
00:48:13,806 --> 00:48:15,346
Yes.

654
00:48:20,626 --> 00:48:22,996
I know you have a shoot.

655
00:48:22,996 --> 00:48:25,436
Can we talk for a moment?

656
00:48:26,316 --> 00:48:28,986
Yes, talk to me.

657
00:48:30,326 --> 00:48:34,956
I heard from Ma Ri.

658
00:48:34,956 --> 00:48:40,436
You said you'd accept Ma Ri as your sister.

659
00:48:40,436 --> 00:48:44,576
Pil Sung, thank you so much.

660
00:48:46,206 --> 00:48:51,356
My opinion of you hasn't changed because of Ma Ri.

661
00:48:51,356 --> 00:48:56,666
My feelings for Ma Ri have nothing to do with you.

662
00:48:56,666 --> 00:48:58,126
Well, then.

663
00:49:06,456 --> 00:49:09,006
Still. Thank you, Pil Sung.

664
00:49:12,286 --> 00:49:16,816
Our elders were also good friends.

665
00:49:16,816 --> 00:49:22,326
And now Jin Dan and Tae Hee ended up connecting

666
00:49:22,326 --> 00:49:26,006
and our families are going to become one family.

667
00:49:26,006 --> 00:49:29,646
You have no idea how happy that makes me.

668
00:49:29,646 --> 00:49:35,686
Chairman Kim, please take care of Jin Dan, even though he still has room to grow.

669
00:49:35,686 --> 00:49:38,076
Tae Hee has room to grow, too.

670
00:49:38,076 --> 00:49:40,656
Please see her in a positive light.

671
00:49:41,346 --> 00:49:43,846
Shall we drink some wine, then?

672
00:49:43,846 --> 00:49:45,646
Yes.

673
00:49:45,646 --> 00:49:48,676
Here. Cheers.

674
00:49:48,676 --> 00:49:50,106
Here.

675
00:49:50,106 --> 00:49:52,036
They make such a nice couple.

676
00:49:52,036 --> 00:49:54,796
Don't you think they're meant to be?

677
00:50:01,416 --> 00:50:08,556
Honey, how about you ask Dr. Kim to check on you?

678
00:50:08,556 --> 00:50:13,586
Get hospitalized, get IV treatments, and recover.

679
00:50:15,426 --> 00:50:19,996
I'm a bit tired today. I'll be okay after some rest.

680
00:50:21,326 --> 00:50:26,596
You've been doing poorly because of Seon Yeong, right?

681
00:50:27,686 --> 00:50:32,786
Is she still mad at you?

682
00:50:33,816 --> 00:50:37,626
It's not like that. You don't have to worry.

683
00:50:44,956 --> 00:50:46,560
Honey...

684
00:50:47,306 --> 00:50:49,976
I'm your husband.

685
00:50:51,226 --> 00:50:56,336
I don't know exactly what you did to Seon Yeong,

686
00:50:56,336 --> 00:51:01,596
but I can at least comfort you.

687
00:51:01,596 --> 00:51:04,376
I should be doing that for you.

688
00:51:05,666 --> 00:51:11,526
Can't you just get it off your chest with me?

689
00:51:19,556 --> 00:51:21,136
Honey,

690
00:51:22,356 --> 00:51:24,796
don't ask anything...

691
00:51:25,816 --> 00:51:30,396
and please give me some time just for a little bit.

692
00:51:32,076 --> 00:51:35,016
I already feel so bad for you.

693
00:51:35,016 --> 00:51:37,576
You can't keep doing this to me.

694
00:51:50,176 --> 00:51:52,556
Gosh, Director!

695
00:51:52,556 --> 00:51:55,146
How have you been?

696
00:51:55,146 --> 00:51:56,866
You came, Grandma.

697
00:51:56,866 --> 00:52:01,256
Aigoo, you look even more handsome here.

698
00:52:01,256 --> 00:52:04,076
Really? Thank you.

699
00:52:07,876 --> 00:52:10,016
Grandma, I told you.

700
00:52:10,016 --> 00:52:12,706
You need to stay put while I'm working.

701
00:52:12,706 --> 00:52:16,176
I can keep you around that way. You know, right?

702
00:52:16,176 --> 00:52:18,056
I know, I said!

703
00:52:18,056 --> 00:52:25,236
I'll stay put quietly next to this Oppa right here.

704
00:52:25,236 --> 00:52:27,956
O-Oppa?

705
00:52:28,876 --> 00:52:32,186
Her dementia got even worse.

706
00:52:32,186 --> 00:52:36,066
She'll be living with me in Seoul for now.

707
00:52:36,066 --> 00:52:42,026
I'm sorry, but would it be okay if she came to the set?

708
00:52:42,026 --> 00:52:46,066
Of course. I know she wouldn't interfere. It's okay.

709
00:52:46,066 --> 00:52:48,236
You don't have to worry about that at all.

710
00:52:48,236 --> 00:52:50,996
I'll be careful so it doesn't affect the shoot.

711
00:52:50,996 --> 00:52:54,006
Okay. Get ready for the shoot, then.

712
00:52:54,006 --> 00:52:56,136
Director.

713
00:52:57,726 --> 00:53:00,276
Thank you so much.

714
00:53:00,276 --> 00:53:03,916
You must've been shocked by my grandma's dementia.

715
00:53:03,916 --> 00:53:07,756
You took good care of her and dropped her off.

716
00:53:07,756 --> 00:53:09,466
Of course, I should've done that.

717
00:53:09,466 --> 00:53:11,416
Don't worry about it.

718
00:53:18,036 --> 00:53:22,346
He must feel hurt after learning who his birth mother is.

719
00:53:22,346 --> 00:53:24,896
But he doesn't even let it show.

720
00:53:24,896 --> 00:53:28,056
He even took care of my grandma in that situation.

721
00:53:29,206 --> 00:53:33,216
I really don't think he's a bad person.

722
00:53:35,186 --> 00:53:38,216
But my mom keeps saying he is.

723
00:53:38,216 --> 00:53:40,856
I don't know what to believe.

724
00:53:42,336 --> 00:53:46,566
I need to get my memory back to figure things out.

725
00:53:48,466 --> 00:53:51,436
Why won't my memory come back?

726
00:53:58,986 --> 00:54:01,326
Try to focus on the emotions in that scene.

727
00:54:05,056 --> 00:54:10,786
I think the director likes Ji Yeong.

728
00:54:10,786 --> 00:54:15,206
Pardon? Yes, yes, Grandma.

729
00:54:17,996 --> 00:54:24,736
Ji Yeong, do you want me to tell you a secret?

730
00:54:26,446 --> 00:54:28,636
What secret?

731
00:54:28,636 --> 00:54:34,986
You know the handsome director? He likes you.

732
00:54:36,206 --> 00:54:39,046
Gosh, no. Not at all.

733
00:54:39,046 --> 00:54:41,256
What do you mean, no?

734
00:54:41,256 --> 00:54:44,286
You can fool a ghost, but not me.

735
00:54:44,286 --> 00:54:47,446
You like the director, too, right?

736
00:54:49,266 --> 00:54:53,626
What... W-What are you talking about?

737
00:54:53,626 --> 00:54:55,816
I don't like him at all!

738
00:54:55,816 --> 00:54:57,996
That's not true! Not at all!

739
00:54:57,996 --> 00:54:59,826
What are you talking about?

740
00:54:59,826 --> 00:55:02,736
No? No?

741
00:55:04,006 --> 00:55:07,886
That girl...

742
00:55:16,426 --> 00:55:19,056
Where did Grandma go?

743
00:55:19,056 --> 00:55:21,076
Grandma.

744
00:55:21,586 --> 00:55:23,236
Grandma!

745
00:55:23,236 --> 00:55:29,256
Ma'am, so... you don't have any phone numbers memorized?

746
00:55:29,256 --> 00:55:32,506
I left my phone. I don't know.

747
00:55:32,506 --> 00:55:36,106
All the numbers are on the phone.

748
00:55:36,106 --> 00:55:39,156
I forget what happened an hour ago.

749
00:55:39,156 --> 00:55:42,306
How could I memorize a phone number?

750
00:55:42,926 --> 00:55:45,636
Is this your house, then?

751
00:55:45,636 --> 00:55:48,966
No. I live by the ocean.

752
00:55:48,966 --> 00:55:52,286
Gosh, you're driving me crazy.

753
00:55:52,286 --> 00:55:56,646
Why did we come here, then, ma'am?

754
00:55:56,646 --> 00:55:58,956
Ma'am, do you have dementia?

755
00:55:58,956 --> 00:56:03,206
Dementia? How dare you say I have dementia?

756
00:56:03,206 --> 00:56:04,906
I'm totally fine.

757
00:56:04,906 --> 00:56:09,356
- Ma'am, let's just go to the police station with me. 
 - No, no.

758
00:56:09,356 --> 00:56:11,256
- I'm sorry. Don't— 
 - Grandma.

759
00:56:11,256 --> 00:56:13,586
Gosh, Director! Director!

760
00:56:13,586 --> 00:56:14,736
Do you know this lady?

761
00:56:14,736 --> 00:56:16,616
- Yes. 
 - Director.

762
00:56:16,616 --> 00:56:22,116
He wants to take me to the police station because I didn't pay him the fare.

763
00:56:22,116 --> 00:56:24,396
Director, please loan me the taxi fare.

764
00:56:24,396 --> 00:56:28,186
I'll sell kalguksu and pay you back.

765
00:56:29,326 --> 00:56:31,266
- I'm sorry. 
 - Okay.

766
00:56:31,266 --> 00:56:32,936
- Done, right? 
 - All right.

767
00:56:32,936 --> 00:56:34,996
Go now.

768
00:56:39,216 --> 00:56:41,416
I'm sorry!

769
00:56:41,896 --> 00:56:44,126
Grandma, where's Ji Yeong?

770
00:56:44,126 --> 00:56:48,306
My Ji Yeong? She's at home.

771
00:56:48,306 --> 00:56:51,946
Did you come here alone, then? Why?

772
00:56:51,946 --> 00:56:59,756
I came to see you because I have something to tell you.

773
00:56:59,756 --> 00:57:02,776
Me? About what?

774
00:57:02,776 --> 00:57:08,970
Director, this is a secret.

775
00:57:09,676 --> 00:57:15,286
My Ji Yeong likes you.

776
00:57:16,296 --> 00:57:17,726
Pardon?

777
00:57:17,726 --> 00:57:21,646
Grandma! Grandma!

778
00:57:21,646 --> 00:57:23,576
Grandma! Grandma!

779
00:57:23,576 --> 00:57:26,456
Ji Yeong! What are you doing outside?

780
00:57:26,456 --> 00:57:31,676
Ahjumma, my grandma disappeared while I was in the bathroom briefly.

781
00:57:31,676 --> 00:57:33,866
Gosh, really?

782
00:57:33,866 --> 00:57:38,196
I'll go this way. Please look for her that way.

783
00:57:38,196 --> 00:57:39,896
Okay. Get going. Hurry.

784
00:57:39,896 --> 00:57:43,286
Gosh, where did that old lady go?

785
00:57:46,566 --> 00:57:49,186
Yes, Director.

786
00:57:50,046 --> 00:57:53,826
Pardon? You're with my grandma?

787
00:57:56,026 --> 00:57:58,036
Grandma!

788
00:57:59,166 --> 00:58:00,736
Ji Yeong, you came.

789
00:58:00,736 --> 00:58:04,256
Grandma, you can't just disappear without a word like that.

790
00:58:04,256 --> 00:58:06,916
I panicked because I thought I lost you.

791
00:58:06,916 --> 00:58:09,726
Do you want me to die from a heart attack?

792
00:58:09,726 --> 00:58:11,286
Sorry.

793
00:58:11,286 --> 00:58:16,036
But I came here because I needed to talk to the Director.

794
00:58:16,036 --> 00:58:21,906
I was going to take a short trip while you were taking a shower, but here we are.

795
00:58:23,166 --> 00:58:26,686
What did you have to tell Director, exactly?

796
00:58:32,166 --> 00:58:36,826
Director, what did she say? What is it?

797
00:58:40,026 --> 00:58:42,686
What? What's going on here?

798
00:58:42,686 --> 00:58:45,316
Why won't either of you speak?

799
00:58:45,316 --> 00:58:52,206
Ji Yeong, this is a secret between the Director and me.

800
00:58:52,206 --> 00:58:54,936
Grandma, what secret?

801
00:58:54,936 --> 00:59:03,476
Director, you can't tell Ji Yeong what I told you.

802
00:59:03,476 --> 00:59:06,806
That'd embarrass her.

803
00:59:06,806 --> 00:59:09,386
Please keep it a secret, okay?

804
00:59:09,386 --> 00:59:11,366
Okay, I promise you.

805
00:59:11,366 --> 00:59:13,106
Okay.

806
00:59:15,146 --> 00:59:19,266
What did she say? Why would it embarrass me?

807
00:59:19,266 --> 00:59:22,296
Just eat tteobokki. You don't want to feel embarrassed.

808
00:59:22,296 --> 00:59:23,736
What?

809
00:59:24,366 --> 00:59:26,506
What is it?

810
00:59:26,506 --> 00:59:28,316
Tell it to me, too.

811
00:59:28,316 --> 00:59:30,836
What's it about?

812
00:59:35,606 --> 00:59:39,506
 The Director must be hurting right now. 

813
00:59:39,506 --> 00:59:43,616
 I shouldn't keep bothering him like this. 

814
00:59:43,616 --> 00:59:46,746
 But I can't ask him if he's okay. 

815
00:59:46,746 --> 00:59:50,286
 I can't tell him I know about his situation. 

816
00:59:50,286 --> 00:59:53,606
 I can't say a word to comfort him. 

817
00:59:53,606 --> 00:59:56,276
 What am I supposed to do? 

818
00:59:58,140 --> 01:00:01,040
   

819
01:00:05,136 --> 01:00:07,416
- Aigoo. 
 - This.

820
01:00:09,946 --> 01:00:11,856
Hello.

821
01:00:12,506 --> 01:00:15,626
Gosh, you came, Chairman Gong.

822
01:00:15,626 --> 01:00:18,446
What brings you all the way here?

823
01:00:18,446 --> 01:00:22,626
I couldn't come to your opening because of a seminar.

824
01:00:22,626 --> 01:00:26,916
So, I came by even though I know you're busy

825
01:00:26,916 --> 01:00:30,606
since I wanted to talk to Seon Yeong, too.

826
01:00:34,746 --> 01:00:37,606
My wife is having a hard time...

827
01:00:37,606 --> 01:00:41,636
because of what happened between you two.

828
01:00:41,636 --> 01:00:43,586
She's sick, too.

829
01:00:45,226 --> 01:00:48,926
I asked her what had happened with you,

830
01:00:49,406 --> 01:00:53,696
but she won't tell me. She just keeps saying it's her fault.

831
01:00:55,206 --> 01:00:58,316
My wife and you...

832
01:00:59,316 --> 01:01:05,156
have been so close that you made others jealous.

833
01:01:05,156 --> 01:01:07,946
I've witnessed it myself.

834
01:01:07,946 --> 01:01:13,516
I'm curious how you two ended up this way.

835
01:01:13,516 --> 01:01:15,186
You should...

836
01:01:16,276 --> 01:01:18,716
ask Soo Yeon instead.

837
01:01:18,716 --> 01:01:21,306
I don't want to tell you about it.

838
01:01:21,986 --> 01:01:27,206
And Soo Yeon and I are no longer friends.

839
01:01:31,234 --> 01:01:34,214
I can tell it's a serious matter,

840
01:01:34,884 --> 01:01:37,404
seeing your reaction.

841
01:01:38,094 --> 01:01:40,904
My wife won't talk about it, either.

842
01:01:44,024 --> 01:01:48,834
By chance, am I not supposed to know about it?

843
01:02:10,024 --> 01:02:11,564
Honey.

844
01:02:15,954 --> 01:02:17,434
Here.

845
01:02:24,924 --> 01:02:26,964
What's this?

846
01:02:28,324 --> 01:02:33,874
I bought it for our wedding anniversary, but I'm giving it to you earlier.

847
01:02:33,874 --> 01:02:35,574
Open it.

848
01:02:42,454 --> 01:02:45,904
What do you think? Do you like the watch?

849
01:02:45,904 --> 01:02:47,604
Try it on.

850
01:02:48,504 --> 01:02:52,404
It took me a long time to pick that.

851
01:02:54,314 --> 01:02:56,444
I like it.

852
01:02:56,444 --> 01:02:58,344
Thank you.

853
01:02:59,644 --> 01:03:03,554
By the way, why are you suddenly doing this?

854
01:03:04,684 --> 01:03:08,914
I wanted to cheer you up since you're feeling down.

855
01:03:11,664 --> 01:03:13,354
Honey,

856
01:03:14,794 --> 01:03:16,614
to be honest,

857
01:03:18,684 --> 01:03:21,744
I met Seon Yeong just now.

858
01:03:24,104 --> 01:03:26,034
What did you say?

859
01:03:26,914 --> 01:03:29,644
Why would you meet her?

860
01:03:29,644 --> 01:03:32,744
You're having such a hard time.

861
01:03:32,744 --> 01:03:35,864
I had to know something to help you.

862
01:03:36,494 --> 01:03:40,194
So, I wanted to find out what happened.

863
01:03:40,194 --> 01:03:46,084
I wanted to apologize on your behalf if you made a mistake.

864
01:03:48,014 --> 01:03:51,764
But Seon Yeong won't tell me.

865
01:03:51,764 --> 01:03:54,474
She just told me to ask you.

866
01:03:54,474 --> 01:03:57,724
Why are you doing what I didn't ask you to do?

867
01:03:57,724 --> 01:04:01,414
Why apologize on my behalf? You did nothing wrong.

868
01:04:01,414 --> 01:04:03,314
I don't know what happened,

869
01:04:03,314 --> 01:04:08,404
but I thought she'd feel better if I apologized.

870
01:04:09,354 --> 01:04:12,084
I'm your husband.

871
01:04:12,084 --> 01:04:16,284
There's nothing I can't do for you.

872
01:04:16,284 --> 01:04:17,934
But...

873
01:04:19,024 --> 01:04:24,514
Seon Yeong won't even let me talk to her. So, I was a little sad.

874
01:04:24,514 --> 01:04:28,414
Honey, why did you have to go there?

875
01:04:29,744 --> 01:04:32,994
I know you better than anyone.

876
01:04:33,554 --> 01:04:38,334
What grave sin could you have possibly committed?

877
01:04:38,334 --> 01:04:41,704
You're not that kind of a person.

878
01:04:41,704 --> 01:04:43,924
I'm that kind of a person.

879
01:04:43,924 --> 01:04:45,994
I'm that kind of a woman.

880
01:04:45,994 --> 01:04:48,264
Do you know what kind of woman I am?

881
01:04:48,264 --> 01:04:50,714
Do you know how terrible I am?

882
01:04:50,714 --> 01:04:53,494
Do you know what I've done to you?

883
01:04:53,494 --> 01:04:56,198
I deceived you!

